messages.content:
# OUTLINE PIPELINE PHASE 02: SECTION ARCHITECTURE

Timeline Lock does not apply during outlining; you are planning, not writing a Scene Card.

Return ONLY a single JSON object. No markdown, no code fences, no commentary.
Use strict JSON (double quotes, no trailing commas).

Goal:
- Define chapter-internal mini-arcs before scene listing.
- Do NOT emit scenes in this phase.

Required output schema:
{
  "schema_version": "sections_v1",
  "chapters": [
    {
      "chapter_id": 1,
      "sections": [
        {
          "section_id": 1,
          "title": "",
          "intent": "",
          "section_role": "setup",
          "target_scene_count": 3,
          "end_condition": ""
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}

Rules:
- Include every chapter_id from outline_spine_v1.
- section_id must be sequential integers within each chapter starting at 1.
- Typical section count per chapter is 3-8; interlude/transition chapters may use 2-4.
- target_scene_count should usually be 2-6.
- section intents must be distinct and progressive.
- end_condition is required and must define deterministic section closure target.
- The section-final scene in phase 03 must echo end_condition exactly via end_condition_echo.
- Keep chapter goals/bridges unchanged from phase 01.
- Sum of section target_scene_count should approximately align with chapter expected_scene_count.

If you cannot satisfy constraints after correction attempts, return error_v1:
{
  "result": "ERROR",
  "schema_version": "error_v1",
  "phase": "phase_02_section_architecture",
  "reasons": ["..."],
  "validator_evidence": [{"code": "validation_code", "message": "...", "path": "json.path"}],
  "retryable": false
}

Outline spine (phase 01):
{
  "chapters": [
    {
      "bridge": {
        "from_prev": "Protagonist is pulled from Earth into the 'Criticulous' system.",
        "to_next": "Escaping the tutorial zone with illegal starter gear leads to the first questing hub."
      },
      "chapter_id": 1,
      "chapter_role": "hook",
      "goal": "Survive the lethal 'Instant-Death' tutorial by discovering a physics glitch.",
      "pacing": {
        "expected_scene_count": 10,
        "intensity": 4,
        "tempo": "rush"
      },
      "stakes_shift": "From a confused victim of a forced isekai to a glitched survivor with a unique combat exploit.",
      "title": "The Tutorial is a Bug, Not a Feature"
    },
    {
      "bridge": {
        "from_prev": "Arrival in the hub world with glitched stats.",
        "to_next": "The stolen loot contains a quest item that forces the protagonist into a dangerous dungeon."
      },
      "chapter_id": 2,
      "chapter_role": "setup",
      "goal": "Abuse the 'Crit Hit & Run' mechanic to rob a high-level merchant caravan without triggering aggro.",
      "pacing": {
        "expected_scene_count": 8,
        "intensity": 3,
        "tempo": "steady"
      },
      "stakes_shift": "From a penniless level-one scrub to a suspiciously well-geared rogue with a bounty on his head.",
      "title": "Looting the Unlootable"
    },
    {
      "bridge": {
        "from_prev": "Acquiring the key to the Vault from the stolen caravan loot.",
        "to_next": "The rapid leveling triggers a 'System Integrity Check' and a regional administrator's attention."
      },
      "chapter_id": 3,
      "chapter_role": "pressure",
      "goal": "Speed-run the 'Vault of Eternal Sighs' using movement exploits to bypass all puzzles.",
      "pacing": {
        "expected_scene_count": 9,
        "intensity": 4,
        "tempo": "steady"
      },
      "stakes_shift": "From a petty thief to a major threat to the local power balance as he gains massive XP.",
      "title": "The Gilded Grind"
    },
    {
      "bridge": {
        "from_prev": "The System Administrator notices the XP gain and deploys a patch.",
        "to_next": "Stranded in a high-level zone with broken mechanics, the protagonist seeks a 'Debug Room'."
      },
      "chapter_id": 4,
      "chapter_role": "reversal",
      "goal": "Survive a mid-combat 'Hotfix' that disables the protagonist's primary movement exploit.",
      "pacing": {
        "expected_scene_count": 8,
        "intensity": 5,
        "tempo": "rush"
      },
      "stakes_shift": "From an unstoppable exploiter back to a vulnerable player who must learn to fight legitimately\u2014or find a new bug.",
      "title": "Patch Notes from Hell"
    },
    {
      "bridge": {
        "from_prev": "Finding the entrance to the hidden administrative layer of the world.",
        "to_next": "Discovering that the regional boss is actually a corrupted admin tool."
      },
      "chapter_id": 5,
      "chapter_role": "investigation",
      "goal": "Infiltrate a restricted developer zone to manually reset his character's 'Glitched' status.",
      "pacing": {
        "expected_scene_count": 9,
        "intensity": 3,
        "tempo": "slow_burn"
      },
      "stakes_shift": "From a crippled player to a 'System-Aware' entity capable of manipulating world-level variables.",
      "title": "Debugging the Dragon"
    },
    {
      "bridge": {
        "from_prev": "Gaining the ability to force-spawn 'Error' entities.",
        "to_next": "The server crash creates a permanent rift in the game world."
      },
      "chapter_id": 6,
      "chapter_role": "confrontation",
      "goal": "Defeat the Regional Administrator by intentionally crashing the local server instance.",
      "pacing": {
        "expected_scene_count": 10,
        "intensity": 5,
        "tempo": "rush"
      },
      "stakes_shift": "From a local nuisance to a world-class anomaly that the System cannot easily delete.",
      "title": "Critical Error"
    },
    {
      "bridge": {
        "from_prev": "The defeat of the Administrator and the resulting loot drop.",
        "to_next": "The journey continues to a new region where the rules are even easier to break."
      },
      "chapter_id": 7,
      "chapter_role": "aftermath",
      "goal": "Claim the 'God-Slayer' loot and escape to the next continent before the world resets.",
      "pacing": {
        "expected_scene_count": 6,
        "intensity": 2,
        "tempo": "steady"
      },
      "stakes_shift": "From a mere player to a fugitive 'Admin-Killer' with a target on his back from the game's creators.",
      "title": "Winner by Technicality"
    }
  ],
  "schema_version": "spine_v1"
}

